		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/December_15&quot; title=&quot;December 15&quot;&gt;December 15&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;: &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Koninkrijksdag&quot; title=&quot;Koninkrijksdag&quot;&gt;Kingdom Day&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; in Aruba, Curaçao, the Netherlands, and Sint Maarten (&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/1954&quot; title=&quot;1954&quot;&gt;1954&lt;/a&gt;); &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Zamenhof_Day&quot; title=&quot;Zamenhof Day&quot;&gt;Zamenhof Day&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Esperanto_culture&quot; title=&quot;Esperanto culture&quot;&gt;Esperanto culture&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;float:right;margin-left:0.5em;&quot; id=&quot;mp-otd-img&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;thumbinner mp-thumb&quot; style=&quot;background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; max-width: 100px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/File:Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; title=&quot;Emperor Hailingwang of Jin&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Emperor Hailingwang of Jin&quot; src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg/100px-Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100&quot; height=&quot;165&quot; srcset=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg/150px-Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg/200px-Wanyan_Digunai_cropped.jpg 2x&quot; data-file-width=&quot;680&quot; data-file-height=&quot;1124&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;thumbcaption&quot; style=&quot;padding: 0.25em 0; word-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;Emperor Hailingwang of Jin&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/1161&quot; title=&quot;1161&quot;&gt;1161&lt;/a&gt; – &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Wanyan_Liang&quot; title=&quot;Wanyan Liang&quot;&gt;Emperor Hailing&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;(bust pictured)&lt;/i&gt; of the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Jin_dynasty_(1115%E2%80%931234)&quot; title=&quot;Jin dynasty (1115–1234)&quot;&gt;Jin dynasty&lt;/a&gt; was assassinated in a military camp near the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Yangtze_River&quot; class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;Yangtze River&quot;&gt;Yangtze River&lt;/a&gt; front following Jin losses in the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Battle_of_Caishi&quot; title=&quot;Battle of Caishi&quot;&gt;Battle of Caishi&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/1791&quot; title=&quot;1791&quot;&gt;1791&lt;/a&gt; – The first ten &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Constitutional_amendment&quot; title=&quot;Constitutional amendment&quot;&gt;amendments&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/United_States_Constitution&quot; title=&quot;United States Constitution&quot;&gt;United States Constitution&lt;/a&gt;, collectively known as the &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/United_States_Bill_of_Rights&quot; title=&quot;United States Bill of Rights&quot;&gt;Bill of Rights&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;, were ratified.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/1906&quot; title=&quot;1906&quot;&gt;1906&lt;/a&gt; – The &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Great_Northern,_Piccadilly_and_Brompton_Railway&quot; title=&quot;Great Northern, Piccadilly and Brompton Railway&quot;&gt;Great Northern, Piccadilly and Brompton Railway&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;, a 14.17-kilometre (8.80&amp;#160;mi) long deep-level underground tube railway connecting &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Hammersmith&quot; title=&quot;Hammersmith&quot;&gt;Hammersmith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Finsbury_Park,_London&quot; title=&quot;Finsbury Park, London&quot;&gt;Finsbury Park, London&lt;/a&gt;, opened.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/1946&quot; title=&quot;1946&quot;&gt;1946&lt;/a&gt; – US-backed Iranian troops brought an end to the &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Iran_crisis_of_1946&quot; title=&quot;Iran crisis of 1946&quot;&gt;Iran crisis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; when they marched upon the breakaway &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Republic_of_Mahabad&quot; title=&quot;Republic of Mahabad&quot;&gt;Republic of Mahabad&lt;/a&gt; and recaptured the territory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/1961&quot; title=&quot;1961&quot;&gt;1961&lt;/a&gt; – Former Nazi leader &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Adolf_Eichmann&quot; title=&quot;Adolf Eichmann&quot;&gt;Adolf Eichmann&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; was sentenced to death after being found guilty on fifteen criminal charges, including &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/War_crime&quot; title=&quot;War crime&quot;&gt;war crimes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Crime_against_humanity&quot; class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;Crime against humanity&quot;&gt;crimes against humanity&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;margin-top: 0.5em;&quot;&gt;
